   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "setup-header"
   },
   "source": [
    "# XML System Prompt Fine-Tuning Workflow\n",
    "## Three-Step Demo: Test Base → Fine-Tune → Test Fine-Tuned\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates training a model to follow XML-based system prompts using unsloth for efficient fine-tuning.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:**\n",
    "1. 🧪 **Baseline Test** - Run inference on base Llama model\n",
    "2. 🔧 **Fine-Tuning** - Train with unsloth on synthetic banking conversations\n",
    "3. 📊 **Evaluation Test** - Run inference on fine-tuned model and compare"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "setup"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Setup: Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "install-deps",
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -q torch transformers datasets peft trl huggingface-hub\n",
    "!pip install -q git+https://github.com/unslothai/unsloth.git\n",
    "print(\"✓ Dependencies installed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "auth"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Authenticate with Hugging Face\n",
    "Required to access gated models like Llama"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "hf-login"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from huggingface_hub import login\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use your HF token (get from https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens)\n",
    "hf_token = input(\"Enter your Hugging Face token: \")\n",
    "login(token=hf_token)\n",
    "print(\"✓ Authenticated with Hugging Face\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "download-data"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Download Project Data\n",
    "Get training data and configuration from the GitHub repo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "get-project"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clone the project repo\n",
    "os.chdir('/content')\n",
    "if not os.path.exists('sys_ins_training'):\n",
    "    print(\"Cloning project repo...\")\n",
    "    subprocess.run(['git', 'clone', 'https://github.com/user/sys_ins_training.git'], check=False)\n",
    "    os.chdir('sys_ins_training')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    os.chdir('sys_ins_training')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Working directory: {os.getcwd()}\")\n",
    "print(\"Project files:\")\n",
    "for item in ['data', 'src', 'models', 'notebooks']:\n",
    "    if os.path.exists(item):\n",
    "        print(f\"  ✓ {item}/\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "baseline-section"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: 🧪 BASELINE TEST - Test Base Model Before Fine-Tuning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "load-system-prompt"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the XML system prompt\n",
    "with open('data/system_prompt.xml') as f:\n",
    "    system_prompt = f.read()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Loaded system prompt ({len(system_prompt)} bytes)\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nSystem prompt preview:\")\n",
    "print(system_prompt[:300] + \"...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "baseline-test",
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"BASELINE TEST: Loading Base Model\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load base model\n",
    "model_name = \"meta-llama/Llama-2-7b-chat-hf\"\n",
    "print(f\"Loading {model_name}...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\n",
    "tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
    "\n",
    "model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n",
    "    model_name,\n",
    "    torch_dtype=torch.float16,\n",
    "    device_map=\"auto\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Model loaded\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Device: {next(model.parameters()).device}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  dtype: {next(model.parameters()).dtype}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "baseline-inference"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test base model on sample inputs\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"BASELINE INFERENCE: Testing Base Model\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "test_inputs = [\n",
    "    \"Hi, I want to check my account balance.\",\n",
    "    \"My debit card was lost. What should I do?\",\n",
    "    \"I saw a charge I didn't make.\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, user_input in enumerate(test_inputs, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n[Example {i}]\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Input: {user_input}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    prompt = f\"{system_prompt}\\n\\nUser: {user_input}\\nAssistant:\"\n",
    "    inputs = tokenizer.encode(prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model.device)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        outputs = model.generate(\n",
    "            inputs,\n",
    "            max_length=200,\n",
    "            temperature=0.7,\n",
    "            top_p=0.9,\n",
    "            do_sample=True\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0], skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
    "    response = response.split(\"Assistant:\")[-1].strip()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Response: {response[:150]}...\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    baseline_results.append({\n",
    "        \"input\": user_input,\n",
    "        \"response\": response,\n",
    "        \"model\": \"base\"\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n✓ Baseline test complete ({len(baseline_results)} examples)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "finetune-section"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Step 2: 🔧 FINE-TUNING - Train Model with unsloth"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "load-training-data"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "from datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Loading training data...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load training dataset\n",
    "dataset = load_dataset('json', data_files='data/training.jsonl')\n",
    "train_dataset = dataset['train']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Loaded {len(train_dataset)} training examples\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSample training example:\")\n",
    "sample = train_dataset[0]\n",
    "print(f\"  Keys: {list(sample.keys())}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  User (first 100 chars): {sample['user'][:100]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Assistant (first 100 chars): {sample['assistant'][:100]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "setup-lora"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from peft import LoraConfig, get_peft_model\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Setting up LoRA for efficient fine-tuning...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "lora_config = LoraConfig(\n",
    "    r=16,\n",
    "    lora_alpha=32,\n",
    "    target_modules=[\"q_proj\", \"v_proj\"],\n",
    "    lora_dropout=0.05,\n",
    "    bias=\"none\",\n",
    "    task_type=\"CAUSAL_LM\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "model = get_peft_model(model, lora_config)\n",
    "model.print_trainable_parameters()\n",
    "print(\"✓ LoRA configured\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "run-training",
    "colab": {\n",
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from trl import SFTTrainer, SFTConfig\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"FINE-TUNING: Training with unsloth + LoRA\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "training_args = SFTConfig(\n",
    "    output_dir=\"./models/fine_tuned\",\n",
    "    num_train_epochs=1,\n",
    "    per_device_train_batch_size=8,\n",
    "    gradient_accumulation_steps=2,\n",
    "    warmup_ratio=0.03,\n",
    "    learning_rate=2e-4,\n",
    "    weight_decay=0.01,\n",
    "    logging_steps=10,\n",
    "    save_strategy=\"epoch\",\n",
    "    max_seq_length=4096,\n",
    "    dataset_text_field=\"user\",\n",
    "    packing=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "trainer = SFTTrainer(\n",
    "    model=model,\n",
    "    args=training_args,\n",
    "    train_dataset=train_dataset,\n",
    "    tokenizer=tokenizer\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nStarting training...\\n\")\n",
    "trainer.train()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"✓ FINE-TUNING COMPLETE\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save the fine-tuned model\n",
    "model.save_pretrained(\"./models/fine_tuned\")\n",
    "tokenizer.save_pretrained(\"./models/fine_tuned\")\n",
    "print(\"✓ Model checkpoint saved to ./models/fine_tuned\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "eval-section"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Step 3: 📊 EVALUATION TEST - Test Fine-Tuned Model After Fine-Tuning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "load-finetuned"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from peft import PeftModel\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Loading fine-tuned model...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load base model again for inference\n",
    "base_model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n",
    "    model_name,\n",
    "    torch_dtype=torch.float16,\n",
    "    device_map=\"auto\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load LoRA weights\n",
    "fine_tuned_model = PeftModel.from_pretrained(base_model, \"./models/fine_tuned\")\n",
    "fine_tuned_model = fine_tuned_model.merge_and_unload()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ Fine-tuned model loaded and merged\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "evaluation-inference"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"EVALUATION INFERENCE: Testing Fine-Tuned Model\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "evaluation_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, user_input in enumerate(test_inputs, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n[Example {i}]\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Input: {user_input}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    prompt = f\"{system_prompt}\\n\\nUser: {user_input}\\nAssistant:\"\n",
    "    inputs = tokenizer.encode(prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(fine_tuned_model.device)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        outputs = fine_tuned_model.generate(\n",
    "            inputs,\n",
    "            max_length=200,\n",
    "            temperature=0.7,\n",
    "            top_p=0.9,\n",
    "            do_sample=True\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0], skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
    "    response = response.split(\"Assistant:\")[-1].strip()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Response: {response[:150]}...\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    evaluation_results.append({\n",
    "        \"input\": user_input,\n",
    "        \"response\": response,\n",
    "        \"model\": \"fine_tuned\"\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n✓ Evaluation complete ({len(evaluation_results)} examples)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "comparison-section"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Comparison: Before vs After Fine-Tuning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "compare-results"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"BEFORE vs AFTER COMPARISON\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, (base_result, ft_result) in enumerate(zip(baseline_results, evaluation_results), 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{'='*80}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Example {i}: {base_result['input']}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"{'='*80}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n[BASE MODEL - BEFORE Fine-Tuning]\")\n",
    "    print(base_result['response'][:200])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n[FINE-TUNED MODEL - AFTER Fine-Tuning]\")\n",
    "    print(ft_result['response'][:200])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n👉 Observations:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   - Base model length: {len(base_result['response'])} chars\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   - Fine-tuned length: {len(ft_result['response'])} chars\")\n",
    "    if \"Morty\" in ft_result['response']:\n",
    "        print(f\"   ✓ Fine-tuned model mentions character name (Morty)\")\n",
    "    if \"FinBank\" in ft_result['response']:\n",
    "        print(f\"   ✓ Fine-tuned model mentions company name (FinBank)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "save-results"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Save Results for Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "save-json"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create comprehensive results file\n",
    "results = {\n",
    "    \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n",
    "    \"workflow\": \"XML System Prompt Fine-Tuning\",\n",
    "    \"model\": \"Llama-2-7b-chat-hf\",\n",
    "    \"training\": {\n",
    "        \"epochs\": 1,\n",
    "        \"examples\": len(train_dataset),\n",
    "        \"batch_size\": 8,\n",
    "        \"learning_rate\": 2e-4,\n",
    "        \"lora_r\": 16,\n",
    "        \"lora_alpha\": 32\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"baseline_test\": baseline_results,\n",
    "    \"evaluation_test\": evaluation_results,\n",
    "    \"comparison\": {\n",
    "        \"examples_tested\": len(test_inputs),\n",
    "        \"note\": \"See baseline_test vs evaluation_test for before/after responses\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save to file\n",
    "with open('colab_results.json', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(results, f, indent=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ Results saved to colab_results.json\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nResults summary:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Training examples: {results['training']['examples']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Test examples: {len(test_inputs)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Baseline tests: {len(baseline_results)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Evaluation tests: {len(evaluation_results)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "download-results"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Download Results"
   ]
  },
